16:42.435 --> 16:44.469
He's wounded.
We can overpower him.

16:44.471 --> 16:47.438
- No, no. He'll kill us.
- He might kill us anyway.
Come on.

16:47.440 --> 16:49.607
I got an ace up my sleeve.
I've remembered where
I know him from.

16:49.609 --> 16:51.442
- What? Where?
- His name's Kipper.

16:51.444 --> 16:53.778
- Oh, his name you remember?
- Well, I pictured a herring,

16:53.780 --> 16:56.614
- and the book says it's easier
to remember unusual names.
- Oh, my fuck!

16:56.616 --> 16:59.517
- Look, when I tell him--
- Do not fucking tell him.

16:59.519 --> 17:01.786
- What?
- If he knows you,
he'll have to kill you.

17:01.788 --> 17:05.156
- Why?
- Statton, I don't want to die,

17:05.158 --> 17:08.292
and neither do you,
so shut the fuck up,
and follow my lead.

17:08.294 --> 17:09.360
But he--

17:24.677 --> 17:27.612
I think you were right.
I do remember you.

17:27.614 --> 17:33.117
No, I just think
you got one of those faces,
like you said.

17:33.119 --> 17:35.686
How can it be my face
if I remember you?

17:38.224 --> 17:41.659
You...

17:41.661 --> 17:43.494
were at Danno's party.

17:46.399 --> 17:48.166
No, I-- I don't think I was.

17:48.168 --> 17:51.135
Yes! Danno's!

17:51.137 --> 17:52.804
You're the piano tuner guy.

17:52.806 --> 17:54.806
We were doing shots
in the kitchen.

17:54.808 --> 17:59.310
Oh, that Danno, yes.
Yes, I was. Yes.

17:59.312 --> 18:02.213
- Sorry.
- I totally remember you.

18:02.215 --> 18:04.449
So, you live around here?

18:04.451 --> 18:07.518
- Mm-hmm.
- Then why are we in a hotel?

18:09.756 --> 18:11.556
Come on, Statton.

18:11.558 --> 18:14.525
You don't want to die
with a lie on your conscience.

18:14.527 --> 18:17.728
That is true. As a Catholic,
it's highly inadvisable.

18:20.533 --> 18:23.868
I, um, still live
with my wife.

18:23.870 --> 18:27.305
- Oh, Jesus.
- No, we're separated.

18:27.307 --> 18:29.373
I sleep on the sofa
in the living room.

18:29.375 --> 18:31.375
Just hasn't been
the right time to leave.

18:31.377 --> 18:34.312
Sure, you're separated,
but you still live together.

18:34.314 --> 18:37.548
- Totally believable.
- I promise you, she won't
mind me being here.

18:37.550 --> 18:40.651
- I could introduce you,
if you like.
- No, I'm fine, really.

18:43.890 --> 18:47.725
So, uh,
how do you know Danno?

18:47.727 --> 18:49.627
Well, my mate Theo
is his supplier.

18:49.629 --> 18:51.329
You're a drug dealer, too?

18:51.331 --> 18:54.398
No. Theo's a drug dealer.

18:54.400 --> 18:56.634
I would never be
a drug dealer.

18:56.636 --> 18:59.403
It's too fussy.
Might as well be a shopkeeper.

19:00.840 --> 19:03.808
<i>( cell phone ringing )</i>

19:07.413 --> 19:09.280
Oh.

19:09.282 --> 19:11.849
Yeah? What do you got?

19:11.851 --> 19:15.653
Will's brother
is cave-diving in Azerbaijan.

19:15.655 --> 19:18.923
- I'm fucking dying here.
-<i> Yeah, I know.</i>

19:18.925 --> 19:21.225
-<i> I'm exploring other options.</i>
- Like what?

19:21.227 --> 19:25.596
- Theo knows this vet.
- A vet? Victor the vet?

19:25.598 --> 19:27.798
Yeah, I think he said
his name was Victor, yeah.

19:27.800 --> 19:30.268
Well, he's not even a real vet.
He got his diploma
on the Internet.

19:30.270 --> 19:33.704
Well, Theo swears by him.
Said he was a star when
his wee doggie got shot.

19:33.706 --> 19:36.274
I won't see a vet without
proper qualifications.

19:36.276 --> 19:39.610
Hey, that doggie has little
wheels on his back legs now.

19:39.612 --> 19:43.714
Are you telling me
that his last patient
is now a paraplegic?

19:45.318 --> 19:47.952
Yeah, all right,
I'll sort something else out.

19:47.954 --> 19:51.222
And a packet
of chewing gum, please.
Sugar-free.

19:52.792 --> 19:54.492
How's the situation now?

19:54.494 --> 19:57.628
Oh, ahem, yeah,
situation's under control, Dec.

19:57.630 --> 20:00.631
You'll never guess.

20:00.633 --> 20:03.935
Statton and I have met before
at one of Danno's parties.

20:05.505 --> 20:08.372
What the fuck?
Are you a chartered moron?

20:08.374 --> 20:11.442
If he knows you,
he can ID you.

20:11.444 --> 20:13.644
If they can hear you,
don't say a fucking word.

20:16.482 --> 20:19.584
This is why you
are the sidekick.

20:19.586 --> 20:24.355
Fuck you. What do I do?

20:24.357 --> 20:27.692
Well, you're gonna
have to kill 'em.

20:27.694 --> 20:28.960
What?

20:28.962 --> 20:32.997
Well, I, uh--
I've, uh, never--

20:32.999 --> 20:36.801
never really had any experience
in that kind of area before.

20:36.803 --> 20:40.972
Are you trying to tell me
that you have never killed
anyone before?

20:40.974 --> 20:42.506
That's correct.

20:42.508 --> 20:46.310
Jesus. You must have.

20:46.312 --> 20:48.346
- Well, I haven't.
-<i> Are you sure?</i>

20:48.348 --> 20:50.448
Well, I'm pretty sure
I'd remember
that sort of thing.

20:50.450 --> 20:52.984
Jesus, Kipper.

20:52.986 --> 20:56.854
And, um, you know, there's been
a little bit of bonding,

20:56.856 --> 20:59.290
and, uh, reminiscences
and all that.

20:59.292 --> 21:01.726
I have three previous.

21:01.728 --> 21:03.527
I'm on parole.

21:03.529 --> 21:07.031
I will get 20 years
for armed robbery.

21:07.033 --> 21:09.634
I am not gonna do
20 fucking years

21:09.636 --> 21:11.636
'cause you're a French fancy!

21:14.540 --> 21:15.973
All right.

21:17.577 --> 21:18.976
You'll have to kill her, too.

21:18.978 --> 21:22.713
No. No.

21:22.715 --> 21:28.886
-<i> No, no.</i>
- She will see you kill him.

21:28.888 --> 21:31.756
We can't have her being
a witness to that, can we?

21:35.895 --> 21:36.961
I can't do it.

21:39.365 --> 21:41.332
All right, I'll do it,

21:41.334 --> 21:44.068
if you admit
you're the sidekick.

21:44.070 --> 21:47.905
You're wrong.
It got a lot friendly,
and you don't shoot a friend.

21:47.907 --> 21:50.808
I'm a lot less shootable
now that he knows me socially.

21:50.810 --> 21:53.077
No, no, no.
You're wrong.

21:53.079 --> 21:56.414
He can't let you go,
so now he can't let me go.

21:57.817 --> 21:59.483
( Kipper whispering )

21:59.485 --> 22:00.918
As soon as this is through

22:00.920 --> 22:03.754
I'm taking Tina
and the kids...

22:03.756 --> 22:06.824
( continues whispering )

22:13.766 --> 22:16.534
Drop the gun and the phone.

22:18.738 --> 22:22.506
- How did you get that?
- You left it on the chair,
Pirate King.

22:24.977 --> 22:26.977
I am the sidekick.

22:38.958 --> 22:41.592
Hello,
my name's Statton Taylor.
I'm in room 304.

22:41.594 --> 22:43.961
We need police
and ambulance right away.

22:43.963 --> 22:45.863
Oh, thank you very much.
Okay, bye.

22:48.134 --> 22:50.968
Police are on their way up
'cause of the earlier bangs--
shot, shots.

22:50.970 --> 22:52.403
- Statton?
- Hmm?

22:52.405 --> 22:55.039
- Get the gun.
- Oh, right.

23:00.646 --> 23:04.815
Please, give me a chance.
Give me a head start, okay?

23:04.817 --> 23:07.618
I've got kids,
I'm an opera singer, and...

23:07.620 --> 23:09.987
I'm clearly not good
at this.

23:11.991 --> 23:14.992
I'll quit.

23:14.994 --> 23:16.927
I'll go into teaching.

23:23.870 --> 23:26.470
( screaming )

23:26.472 --> 23:30.608
- Police! Get on the floor!
- Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Get on the floor!

23:30.610 --> 23:33.511
Thank Christ you're here!

23:33.513 --> 23:35.813
- What?
- They tried to kill me!
I brought her up to my room,

23:35.815 --> 23:37.548
and she pulled out a gun
and called her boyfriend.

23:37.550 --> 23:40.918
- He was robbing us.
- You get your heads down!

23:40.920 --> 23:43.154
The room's in my name.
My name's Statton Taylor.

23:43.156 --> 23:45.022
Of course it is.
And I'm the one being
held at gunpoint.

23:45.024 --> 23:47.525
- I'm Statton Taylor!
- No, he's not!

23:47.527 --> 23:48.793
- Shut the fuck up!
- Okay, okay, okay.

23:48.795 --> 23:50.494
Have you got any ID, sir?

23:50.496 --> 23:53.063
- Hey, that's my wallet!
- Shut it!

24:00.706 --> 24:04.208
- Any photo ID?
- Ah, Jesus. They're
the ones with the guns.

24:04.210 --> 24:07.812
- Whose ID do you think it is?
- It's mine! He stole
the wallet from me!

24:07.814 --> 24:10.781
Very slowly look up
towards the door.

24:10.783 --> 24:12.817
Sedgwick, manager.

24:12.819 --> 24:15.486
Which one of these men
is Statton Taylor?

24:17.523 --> 24:19.690
- That one.
- What?

24:19.692 --> 24:21.892
- I talked to him earlier.
- Mary: His name is Kipper.

24:21.894 --> 24:24.161
He went to the door.
He had us at gunpoint.

24:24.163 --> 24:26.964
You're the one with the guns.
He's the one that's wounded.

24:26.966 --> 24:31.135
- Twice. Wounded twice.
- We'll get you to the hospital,
Mr. Taylor.

24:31.137 --> 24:33.737
- We'll take a statement
in the morning.
- Thank you, officer.

24:33.739 --> 24:34.772
I thought they
were gonna kill me.

24:34.774 --> 24:37.641
We do our job, that's all.

24:37.643 --> 24:39.944
Sedgwick:
You do not have to
say anything,

24:39.946 --> 24:43.013
but it may harm your defense
if you don't mention
when questioned

24:43.015 --> 24:46.083
something you later
rely on in court.

24:46.085 --> 24:48.152
<i> ( music playing )</i>

25:08.841 --> 25:14.011
Fuck. Statton,
I think I've got a wrap
of coke in my pocket.

25:14.013 --> 25:16.514
What? Cocaine?

25:16.516 --> 25:18.949
Mm-hmm. Can you reach it?
It's in my jacket pocket.

25:18.951 --> 25:22.953
- But they searched you.
- There's a zip pocket
inside the pocket.

25:22.955 --> 25:28.092
- Just leave it there.
- No, no. They might have dogs
at the station.

25:28.094 --> 25:31.161
-<i> ( police radio chatter )</i>
- Why do you have cocaine
anyway? It's illegal.

25:31.163 --> 25:33.797
It's from a party
weeks ago.

25:33.799 --> 25:36.967
- Just get it.
- All right.

25:36.969 --> 25:38.269
God!

25:43.142 --> 25:44.875
I can't.

25:44.877 --> 25:47.878
- That is not my pocket.
- Sorry.

25:47.880 --> 25:49.880
I've got it,
I've got it, I've got it.

25:52.051 --> 25:53.717
Let's hand it in.

25:53.719 --> 25:56.954
No, no. Just drop it
when we get out of the van.

25:56.956 --> 26:00.691
No, you always go
to the authorities, that way
they never suspect you.

26:04.130 --> 26:06.263
- Officer?
- ( banging )

26:06.265 --> 26:09.266
- Officer, I found illegal drugs
in the back of your van.
- Statton, no, no, no.

26:43.603 --> 26:46.370
Not your first time then.

26:46.372 --> 26:49.106
- What?
- We've run a check on your
girlfriend's fingerprints.

26:49.108 --> 26:52.876
- She's not my girlfriend.
- Oh, I'm sorry.
Your "lady friend."

26:52.878 --> 26:55.813
Her name is Yvonne Page,

26:55.815 --> 27:00.284
and she has a previous
for armed robbery.

27:00.286 --> 27:03.087
We're not saying anything
till our lawyer gets here.

27:03.089 --> 27:06.657
- Come back then.
- Oh, I will.

27:22.241 --> 27:24.675
Fucking sidekick.

27:25.411 --> 27:26.910
Fuck.

27:35.421 --> 27:38.155
Where's the leg
that needs fixing then?

27:40.226 --> 27:42.793
Your name's Yvonne?
Your name's not even Carol.

27:42.795 --> 27:44.795
You have previous convictions.

27:44.797 --> 27:46.430
Oh, that's it,
we're going down.

27:46.432 --> 27:48.766
Oh, calm down.
It's not like I planned this.

27:48.768 --> 27:50.934
If I did, I wouldn't
have a criminal record
now, would I?

27:50.936 --> 27:54.104
Still your fault.
You grabbed the gun.
You had the cocaine.

27:54.106 --> 27:56.140
Oh, my God,
I'm going down
for armed robbery.

27:56.142 --> 27:59.677
Oh, my giddy Christ,
why didn't you tell me
you'd already been arrested?

27:59.679 --> 28:02.246
- It was a long time ago. I--
- Well, how long ago?

28:02.248 --> 28:03.914
Was it before
or after the nunnery?

28:03.916 --> 28:07.317
It was actually the reason
I was asked to leave.

28:08.821 --> 28:11.822
You committed armed robbery
when you were a nun?

28:11.824 --> 28:13.824
I just drove the getaway car.

28:13.826 --> 28:15.959
No one thought they'd chase
the convent car.

28:15.961 --> 28:18.462
It had St. Lucy
of the Isle Convent
written all over it.

28:18.464 --> 28:20.097
You were a nun here
on the island?

28:20.099 --> 28:21.832
- Mm-hmm.
- I thought you were a tourist.

28:21.834 --> 28:23.333
I left the island years ago.

28:23.335 --> 28:25.703
I just come back
every now and again.

28:25.705 --> 28:27.938
To wreak havoc
and get people arrested.

28:27.940 --> 28:30.374
Look, you're making
too much of it.

28:30.376 --> 28:33.310
I got a suspended sentence,
I didn't do time.

28:33.312 --> 28:34.978
Who are you even
doing this with?

28:34.980 --> 28:37.114
- Errant nuns who needed--
- No.

28:37.116 --> 28:39.116
I fell in with a bad crowd.

28:39.118 --> 28:41.085
How? You were living
in a convent!

28:41.087 --> 28:44.321
They were a youth group.
Troubled teens.

28:44.323 --> 28:46.724
I was supposed to be
mentoring them,

28:46.726 --> 28:49.159
- but instead--
- Instead, you committed
armed robbery with them.

28:49.161 --> 28:52.229
Oh, they were fun,
and they offered to give me
some of the cash.

28:52.231 --> 28:55.399
You have no idea how hard
the vow of poverty is.

28:55.401 --> 29:01.772
- Fuck-a-fuck.
- Way worse than chastity
by far.

29:01.774 --> 29:03.774
<i> ( phone ringing )</i>

29:08.180 --> 29:10.214
Hello.
Statton Taylor speaking.

29:10.216 --> 29:14.284
- Kipper! What's going on?
- Oh, calm down, mum.

29:14.286 --> 29:17.154
I'm fine, I'm fine.
I'm in the hospital.

29:17.156 --> 29:20.290
- You're not in the nick?
-<i> No. No, no, no.</i>

29:20.292 --> 29:22.459
They caught the pair
that did it.

29:25.364 --> 29:28.899
Are you telling me
the two people that can ID us

29:28.901 --> 29:30.534
are in the fucking nick?

29:30.536 --> 29:32.302
That's right, mum.

29:42.381 --> 29:43.981
<i> You really stupid,</i>
<i> you know that?</i>

29:43.983 --> 29:47.050
I woke Petal up
and got her to put on

29:47.052 --> 29:49.219
a nurse's uniform
to instill confidence in you,

29:49.221 --> 29:51.555
and you're not
even fucking here!

29:51.557 --> 29:53.323
Look, someone with
a first aid certificate

29:53.325 --> 29:56.260
that you do weekly role-play
with is not a nurse.

29:58.063 --> 30:00.230
Mum.

30:00.232 --> 30:03.033
Just get yourself
out of the hospital
as soon as you can,

30:03.035 --> 30:05.536
before
the Bobbsey twins ID you.

30:07.940 --> 30:09.306
Love you, bye.

30:10.242 --> 30:11.408
Prick.

30:15.281 --> 30:16.580
We have to go, Petal.

30:16.582 --> 30:20.083
Shame to waste the bed.

30:20.085 --> 30:25.022
You could be done
in three minutes, Dec-ster.

30:32.932 --> 30:36.300
This can't be happening.
This can't be happening to me.

30:36.302 --> 30:39.169
- This is your fault!
- This is good for you.

30:39.171 --> 30:41.872
You needed
something like this.

30:54.253 --> 30:57.621
I don't want no trouble.
I just wanna go home.

30:57.623 --> 30:59.456
( sobbing )

30:59.458 --> 31:04.628
Seems to me
like you need a new start.

31:04.630 --> 31:07.297
Get your own place.

31:07.299 --> 31:09.132
That problem
seems to be solved.

31:09.134 --> 31:11.134
I'm about to get
a cell of my own.

31:11.136 --> 31:13.136
It'd be better than
what you have.

31:13.138 --> 31:15.138
You got no life.

31:15.140 --> 31:17.574
Don't judge me.
You can't judge me.

31:17.576 --> 31:21.011
I run my own business.
I tune pianos, which is a--

31:21.013 --> 31:22.946
Which is,
when you think about it,

31:22.948 --> 31:25.315
making something
someone else made
very slightly better.

31:25.317 --> 31:28.285
You don't make pianos.
You don't make music.

31:28.287 --> 31:32.356
What the-- I allow
other people to make music.

31:32.358 --> 31:36.026
Well, aren't you tired
of letting other people
make the music?

31:36.028 --> 31:39.663
When I started, there were
a thousand functioning pianos

31:39.665 --> 31:42.232
on this island,
and now there are 400.

31:42.234 --> 31:46.937
I'm not even
a failed musician anymore.
I'm a failed piano tuner.

31:48.340 --> 31:51.341
Except now
I'll be nothing,

31:51.343 --> 31:53.210
because I'll have
a criminal record.

31:53.212 --> 31:56.079
And what school or church
or community hall

31:56.081 --> 31:58.682
is gonna give me the run
of their place, eh?

31:58.684 --> 32:02.953
Because my life,
the one you say I don't have,

32:02.955 --> 32:04.421
will be over.

32:04.423 --> 32:07.190
You're acting like
we're guilty here.

32:07.192 --> 32:09.593
The whole thing
is kinda funny when
you think about it.

32:09.595 --> 32:12.195
The cops arresting us
while the guy was in the room?

32:12.197 --> 32:14.097
That wasn't remotely funny.

32:14.099 --> 32:16.066
And who gives a flying frick
if we're innocent

32:16.068 --> 32:17.434
if we can't prove it?

32:17.436 --> 32:20.704
Look, when our lawyer
gets here, he--

32:20.706 --> 32:23.974
he should be here.
What time is it?

32:23.976 --> 32:26.543
Well, I don't know, because
the very expensive watch

32:26.545 --> 32:28.145
that my wife bought me
has been stolen.

32:28.147 --> 32:30.080
It wasn't expensive.
It was a fake.

32:30.082 --> 32:32.382
My wife bought me that watch
from a very, very--

32:32.384 --> 32:34.685
Then your wife was ripped off.

32:34.687 --> 32:36.987
My dad was a jeweler.

32:36.989 --> 32:38.722
I spent
my childhood in Philly

32:38.724 --> 32:41.491
sitting in
the back of his shop
wearing a loupe.

32:41.493 --> 32:44.461
He called me Diamond Lil'.

32:44.463 --> 32:47.731
My watch might be fake,
but at least I'm not.

32:49.401 --> 32:50.701
What's that supposed to mean?

32:50.703 --> 32:55.238
Mary, Carol,
Yvonne-- whatever.

32:55.240 --> 32:57.607
Is there anything else
you want to tell me?

32:57.609 --> 32:59.409
I don't want
any more surprises.

32:59.411 --> 33:02.245
Well, one thing,

33:02.247 --> 33:05.382
but it's tiny,
not even worth mentioning.

33:05.384 --> 33:08.418
- What?
- It's nothing.

33:08.420 --> 33:10.587
I demand you tell me.

33:10.589 --> 33:13.557
Don't laugh at me.
This is my life!

33:13.559 --> 33:17.127
- It was a bar fight.
- You were in a bar fight.

33:17.129 --> 33:18.762
I was protecting a friend.

33:18.764 --> 33:21.431
Some guy was getting sleazy
with her in the strip club.

33:21.433 --> 33:24.001
What were you doing
in a strip club?

33:24.003 --> 33:26.336
Stripping.

33:30.009 --> 33:31.742
Right.

33:31.744 --> 33:34.578
Okay.

33:34.580 --> 33:36.113
Right.

33:36.115 --> 33:39.783
Was this before
or after the nunnery?

33:39.785 --> 33:42.152
After.

33:42.154 --> 33:45.288
I couldn't pay the bills,
couldn't go home.

33:45.290 --> 33:47.290
Did they know
you were a nun?

33:47.292 --> 33:49.292
That was my act.

33:49.294 --> 33:52.029
- What was?
- Stripping nun.

33:52.031 --> 33:56.666
My character was called
Our Lady Of The Night.

34:07.813 --> 34:09.780
You don't have to stay here
all night, you know.

34:09.782 --> 34:14.184
- Not on my account.
- Don't worry, mate.

34:14.186 --> 34:17.287
Better in here
than it is out there,
I can assure you.

34:17.289 --> 34:19.589
Don't want to stretch
your legs or anything?

34:19.591 --> 34:23.493
Oh, thanks.
I'm meant to be here,

34:23.495 --> 34:27.230
