make me look like a prick

39:30.135 --> 39:32.435
for allowing the two
of you out of the station.

39:34.806 --> 39:36.673
Go.

39:39.511 --> 39:42.779
- Could we go?
- You're still charged with
possession of cocaine.

39:42.781 --> 39:45.648
I think under
the circumstances, Sergeant,

39:45.650 --> 39:47.650
all charges
should be dropped.

39:47.652 --> 39:49.919
Do you?
Sadly, I disagree.

39:49.921 --> 39:54.524
Officer,
the drugs were mine.

39:54.526 --> 39:56.826
Statton had nothing
to do with it.

39:56.828 --> 39:58.528
Well, he was holding them,

39:58.530 --> 40:00.029
which means
you're both in possession

40:00.031 --> 40:02.665
with conspiracy to pervert
the course of justice.

40:02.667 --> 40:06.403
Your bail just doubled,
you numpties!

40:23.555 --> 40:26.790
Dec, I am out. I'm out.

40:26.792 --> 40:30.560
Oh, good. They'll be out
sooner or later, too.

40:30.562 --> 40:31.828
We got to get rid of them.

40:31.830 --> 40:33.463
No, no, no, no,
it's too late.

40:33.465 --> 40:34.664
Too late,
they'll definitely

40:34.666 --> 40:35.865
have talked by now,
definitely.

40:35.867 --> 40:37.033
Yeah, but you can't
have a trial

40:37.035 --> 40:39.035
without witnesses,
can you, buddy?

40:39.037 --> 40:42.906
<i> I told you, right,</i>
<i> not to go into a room</i>

40:42.908 --> 40:45.041
where people
were still awake.

40:45.043 --> 40:47.043
I told you
it was reckless.

40:47.045 --> 40:48.478
But you didn't listen.

40:48.480 --> 40:50.046
It was just meant to be
a bit of fun.

40:50.048 --> 40:51.681
Something funny
to tell the boys.

40:51.683 --> 40:53.583
Yeah, well, I'll tell you
what is funny, okay?

40:53.585 --> 40:55.585
I gotta lay low, Dec? Okay?
The cops are after me

40:55.587 --> 40:57.053
and they don't know
what you look like!

40:57.055 --> 41:01.224
Does your kid know
what you look like?

41:01.226 --> 41:03.092
Because at this rate,
he'll be identifying

41:03.094 --> 41:06.229
your dead body
in the morgue, mate.

41:15.140 --> 41:18.074
Hello, Denise,
I'm sorry to wake you.

41:18.076 --> 41:22.912
Um, I'm in the police station.

41:22.914 --> 41:24.247
I really don't want to ask,

41:24.249 --> 41:30.920
but, uh, could you, um,
bail me out?

41:30.922 --> 41:33.890
And my friend?

41:35.694 --> 41:38.661
- Denise, thanks. Look--
- This your friend?

41:38.663 --> 41:40.630
Yeah.

41:40.632 --> 41:42.565
Can I have a word
with you please?

41:42.567 --> 41:45.168
Um, sure.

42:00.118 --> 42:04.621
Okay, I'll bail you out,
but you got take him.

42:04.623 --> 42:07.290
- What?
- He can't come back to me.

42:07.292 --> 42:08.791
Look, I don't know
what you think this is--

42:08.793 --> 42:10.927
We broke up a year ago--

42:10.929 --> 42:13.563
sorry,
I don't know your name.

42:14.966 --> 42:16.799
Call me Carol.

42:16.801 --> 42:20.136
Carol, please,
we broke up a year ago.

42:20.138 --> 42:22.605
- Got a divorce.
- Well, he said separated.

42:22.607 --> 42:26.709
He always says that.
We signed divorce papers.

42:26.711 --> 42:29.679
He said he was gonna
get his own place,

42:29.681 --> 42:30.813
he was just staying
on the sofa bed

42:30.815 --> 42:32.315
- for a couple of weeks.
- Yeah.

42:32.317 --> 42:34.817
Well, I've started
seeing someone else.

42:34.819 --> 42:37.086
Six months went by,
new guy wants to move in.

42:37.088 --> 42:39.822
- Oh, I see.
- Do you know, tonight
is the first night

42:39.824 --> 42:41.858
that he stayed out
after 10:00?

42:41.860 --> 42:47.830
I was so hopeful.
I thought, "This is it.

42:47.832 --> 42:50.833
He's met someone.
He's gonna go!"

42:50.835 --> 42:52.835
I think it's more
of a one-night kinda--

42:52.837 --> 42:54.837
No. No, it can't be.

42:54.839 --> 42:57.707
I'll pay you to be
his transitional girl.

42:57.709 --> 42:58.942
I mean, I'll bail you out.

42:58.944 --> 43:00.610
Well, can't you just
ask him to leave?

43:00.612 --> 43:06.049
I've tried to!
He just keeps not leaving.

43:06.051 --> 43:09.852
I have come home
furious as fuck,

43:09.854 --> 43:12.188
ready to throw him out,
change the locks,

43:12.190 --> 43:14.724
and he's just...

43:14.726 --> 43:16.192
he's cooked a risotto,

43:16.194 --> 43:19.329
changed my light bulbs.

43:19.331 --> 43:21.364
He's just not
the sort of guy

43:21.366 --> 43:25.201
who you can throw out.

43:25.203 --> 43:28.037
But now, now!
This is his own fault,
you know.

43:28.039 --> 43:30.873
I can do this now.
It might be my last shot.

43:30.875 --> 43:34.043
- I don't know.
- Skip bail if you want.

43:34.045 --> 43:35.378
Get the ferry
to the mainland.

43:35.380 --> 43:37.347
I don't care,
just take him with you.

43:37.349 --> 43:40.116
I beg you.

43:47.359 --> 43:50.393
Do you take plastic?

43:51.763 --> 43:53.229
You're throwing me out?

43:53.231 --> 43:56.399
No, you're leaving me
for her.

43:56.401 --> 43:57.900
But I need to come home.
I just got robbed.

43:57.902 --> 44:00.403
I haven't got any money.

44:00.405 --> 44:02.071
All right, you can have
what I've got in my purse,

44:02.073 --> 44:03.773
then call the bank tomorrow.

44:03.775 --> 44:07.076
You're in luck. Here's 100.
Good luck, Statton.

44:07.078 --> 44:09.912
- What about my stuff, my--
- I'll send it on.

44:13.251 --> 44:16.052
Where to?

44:16.053 --> 44:18.854
Babe, ask Carol, huh?
You live with her now.

44:27.932 --> 44:30.099
