- I gotta go.
- Wait, you haven't heard
the story yet.

50:59.323 --> 51:00.389
Tell her the story.

51:02.560 --> 51:06.729
<i> ¶ 'Cause I'm gonna fight</i>
<i> for love ¶</i>

51:08.232 --> 51:10.366
( no audible dialogue )

51:13.204 --> 51:17.573
<i> ( electric guitar</i>
<i> warming up )</i>

51:21.679 --> 51:25.581
<i> ( rock music playing )</i>

51:28.553 --> 51:30.719
Motherfucker!

51:33.691 --> 51:35.191
( screaming )

51:39.764 --> 51:41.497
No, no, no, no.
I attacked him in front

51:41.499 --> 51:43.532
of a police officer
completely unprovoked.

51:43.534 --> 51:45.334
- I have to plead guilty.
- You never have to
plead guilty.

51:45.336 --> 51:46.869
I want to plead guilty.

51:46.871 --> 51:49.238
It was the greatest moment
of my life.

51:49.240 --> 51:50.539
I don't want to deny it.

51:50.541 --> 51:53.542
Hey, guilty makes
my life easy.

51:53.544 --> 51:56.145
And the police are
looking for Mary, right?

51:56.147 --> 51:58.714
Oh! Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

51:58.716 --> 52:01.383
If you want my advice,
as a legal professional,

52:01.385 --> 52:03.152
don't worry about her.

52:03.154 --> 52:05.221
She's a very
capable lady, mm-hmm. Eh?

52:07.758 --> 52:11.260
So, how long
are we gonna wait here?

52:11.262 --> 52:14.163
Until Kipper calls us back
and decides what
to do with you.

52:21.405 --> 52:23.572
We shouldn't have left
Asbo at the bar.

52:23.574 --> 52:25.174
Well, there's a new scent
in the car, man.

52:25.176 --> 52:27.143
Do you want him barking,
drawing attention?

52:27.145 --> 52:30.146
Theo: He doesn't like
being tied up, though.
You know that.

52:30.148 --> 52:32.648
- He's a dog, man!
- Yeah, but dogs have feelings.

52:47.598 --> 52:48.898
Hmm.

52:51.369 --> 52:53.836
( chewing loudly )

52:56.307 --> 52:57.640
Can I have some gum?

53:04.615 --> 53:05.681
Thanks.

53:15.459 --> 53:19.461
So what's it like,
being a dealer?

53:19.463 --> 53:22.965
- It's a living.
- It's not like being
a shopkeeper then?

53:22.967 --> 53:26.635
Did Kipper say that?
Is he still going on
about that?

53:26.637 --> 53:29.805
I've told him before,
it's a dangerous game.

53:29.807 --> 53:31.974
It's not like running
a Tesco Metro!

53:31.976 --> 53:34.810
- Jesus Christ!
- Well, he didn't
say that exactly.

53:34.812 --> 53:36.245
Oh, yes, he did.
I know him.

53:36.247 --> 53:37.646
Don't let her wind you up.

53:37.648 --> 53:40.816
I'm sorry.
I should have said anything.

53:40.818 --> 53:44.253
I'm just thinking of
a career change, that's all.

53:46.657 --> 53:49.491
Can you really buy a degree?

53:49.493 --> 53:52.828
I didn't
buy a degree, right?
I did a course.

53:52.830 --> 53:55.998
On the Internet.
Distance learning
is the future.

53:56.000 --> 53:59.368
That's what I told Kipper,
and he said an Internet degree

53:59.370 --> 54:01.670
is not worth the email
it's attached to.

54:01.672 --> 54:04.506
- Fucking Kipper!
- You know, you guys
shouldn't worry

54:04.508 --> 54:07.009
about anything that guy says.

54:07.011 --> 54:09.511
He got shot
in the leg tonight--

54:09.513 --> 54:12.014
twice--
trying to rob a hotel.

54:12.016 --> 54:15.684
I mean, who does
he think he is, Al Capone?

54:15.686 --> 54:17.686
Oh, he's a fucking amateur.

54:17.688 --> 54:19.688
And "Kipper"?
What's with that name?

54:19.690 --> 54:21.857
It's a nickname.
Do you wanna know
how he got it?

54:21.859 --> 54:24.693
Oh, my God, so much.
Is it embarrassing?

54:24.695 --> 54:26.629
Oh, you have no idea.

54:44.048 --> 54:46.315
( burps )

54:56.060 --> 54:59.561
Dec wants you dead, kid.
He won't do 20 years.

54:59.563 --> 55:02.064
So, get on the first ferry
to the mainland
in the morning, okay?

55:02.066 --> 55:05.567
Okay, I will. Thanks, guys.

55:05.569 --> 55:09.071
And if you are gonna
make those Welsh cakes,
don't forget...

55:09.073 --> 55:12.441
- grease the griddle pan--
- With lard!

55:12.443 --> 55:13.976
Oh, come here.

55:21.752 --> 55:24.586
And by the way, it was me

55:24.588 --> 55:26.422
who did the stripping nun act.

55:26.424 --> 55:28.924
I knew it!

55:38.769 --> 55:42.771
- Well, look who's
in trouble again.
- Mary!

55:42.773 --> 55:45.074
Oh, thank God.
I was so worried.

55:45.076 --> 55:49.912
- What are you doing here?
- Someone had to bail you out.

55:49.914 --> 55:54.016
- You don't have any money.
- Will you take plastic?

55:58.789 --> 56:02.624
Thank you, Reverend Mother.
I really appreciate this.

56:02.626 --> 56:04.626
Don't thank me,
thank Father Donald.

56:04.628 --> 56:09.031
- It's his credit card.
- He always had a crush on me.

56:12.636 --> 56:15.971
Father Donald better get
every penny of this back,

56:15.973 --> 56:19.842
- and some reward points.
- ( laughs )

56:23.414 --> 56:28.650
- Where are you taking me?
- Please, just follow me, okay?

56:28.652 --> 56:32.821
We should find
somewhere to hide
until the first ferry.

56:32.823 --> 56:36.992
I am getting off
this God forsaken island
and never coming back.

56:36.994 --> 56:39.995
Well, I can't leave, can I?
Where would I go?

56:39.997 --> 56:42.931
Um, somewhere where
no one wants to kill you?

56:42.933 --> 56:48.537
- I don't have--
- Statton, when was
the last time

56:48.539 --> 56:50.005
you went to the mainland?

56:50.007 --> 56:54.843
Uh, probably my stag night?

56:54.845 --> 56:57.179
I don't remember much
of that, to be honest.

56:57.181 --> 57:02.184
- And how long ago was that?
- Uh, eight years ago.

57:02.186 --> 57:05.687
Eight years?
Wait, you haven't been
off this tiny island

57:05.689 --> 57:06.755
in eight years?

57:08.025 --> 57:09.558
I haven't really
had the time.

57:09.560 --> 57:11.727
Yes, you have.

57:11.729 --> 57:13.896
When was the last time
you lived somewhere else?

57:13.898 --> 57:16.932
Did you go away
to college or...

57:19.570 --> 57:22.204
You've never lived
anywhere else but here?

57:22.206 --> 57:24.039
All right, that's it, buddy.

57:24.041 --> 57:26.575
We are getting off
this island if we have
to swim for it.

57:26.577 --> 57:28.043
No, no, no, no.
Wait, please.

57:28.045 --> 57:31.947
Just... it's a surprise.

57:34.585 --> 57:36.585
All in all,
I'd say I'm very good

57:36.587 --> 57:39.488
- for surprises this evening.
- One more?

57:40.591 --> 57:42.891
Okay.

57:55.906 --> 57:59.975
( bells tolling )

58:03.614 --> 58:05.247
The convent?

58:05.249 --> 58:08.517
Just wait in the chapel.
I'll be back.

58:23.934 --> 58:27.269
Hi, sorry to bother you.
My name's Statton.

58:27.271 --> 58:30.205
Um, I actually went
to Sunday school here.

58:30.207 --> 58:32.274
Um, that's irrelevant.

58:32.276 --> 58:36.945
Um, I'm a friend--
an acquaintance of Dec...lan?

58:36.947 --> 58:38.914
Don't know no Declan.

58:38.916 --> 58:41.884
Scottish?
Very-- quite angry.

58:41.886 --> 58:44.653
He said you might have
a necklace.

58:44.655 --> 58:46.221
Don't know
about no necklace.

58:46.223 --> 58:50.526
- And the pendant or...
- Eh.

58:50.528 --> 58:53.195
Are you sure?
'Cause, I mean,
he was quite adamant.

58:53.197 --> 58:56.798
All right, all right.

58:56.800 --> 58:58.867
I had it, but I haven't
got it anymore.

58:58.869 --> 59:03.305
Oh. Where is it?

59:03.307 --> 59:06.008
Give me a minute.
I'll call the guy
and get it back to you.

59:06.010 --> 59:07.743
Oh, thank you very much.

59:07.745 --> 59:10.312
It'll cost you.
500 at least.

59:10.314 --> 59:14.016
- Sure.
- Wait in the chapel.

59:14.985 --> 59:16.685
Are you online?

59:16.687 --> 59:18.921
I could do
a bank transfer, you see?

59:41.345 --> 59:43.779
Who's that?

59:43.781 --> 59:47.849
- Saint Tropez.
- Oh, yeah.

59:47.851 --> 59:49.851
Patron saint of suntans.

59:49.853 --> 59:52.854
Heh. Suntans?

59:52.856 --> 59:56.291
Okay, but it is Saint Tropez.

59:56.293 --> 1:00:00.028
He was decapitated by Nero,

1:00:00.030 --> 1:00:03.966
who set him adrift in a boat
with a rooster and a dog.

1:00:03.968 --> 1:00:06.668
Rougher night than ours.

1:00:06.670 --> 1:00:11.873
So, what's all the mystery?
What's the big surprise?

1:00:11.875 --> 1:00:14.209
Have you resubmitted
my application to the convent?

1:00:14.211 --> 1:00:17.012
'Cause I really don't think
they're gonna reconsider.

1:00:17.014 --> 1:00:21.083
Just... wait and see.

1:00:24.221 --> 1:00:26.388
Kipper, they're here.

1:00:26.390 --> 1:00:27.956
I don't know how long
I can hold them.

1:00:31.061 --> 1:00:34.229
Okay, confess something.

1:00:34.231 --> 1:00:38.233
Um, if a customer upsets me

1:00:38.235 --> 1:00:43.405
sometimes I make
their D slightly sharp.

1:00:43.407 --> 1:00:47.109
- True.
- True.

1:00:47.111 --> 1:00:52.114
I had an affair with
my math teacher's wife.

1:00:52.116 --> 1:00:56.652
- That's gotta be false.
- True.

1:00:56.654 --> 1:00:59.354
Sometimes when
I run out of underwear,

1:00:59.356 --> 1:01:02.257
I'd borrow
my wife's boyfriend's.

1:01:02.259 --> 1:01:05.827
- Um, true.
- True.

1:01:05.829 --> 1:01:08.096
When I was a nun,

1:01:08.098 --> 1:01:10.098
I was in a death metal band

1:01:10.100 --> 1:01:12.200
called "Clitty Slickers."

1:01:12.202 --> 1:01:14.369
True. Definitely true.

1:01:14.371 --> 1:01:18.807
- False.
- I wasn't sure you were
telling the truth

1:01:18.809 --> 1:01:22.844
about being a nun until
Mother Superior turned up.

1:01:22.846 --> 1:01:25.113
Okay.

1:01:25.115 --> 1:01:26.815
Well, I didn't believe
for one minute

1:01:26.817 --> 1:01:28.884
you were really
separated from your wife.

1:01:33.190 --> 1:01:36.058
What was your worst
relationship?

1:01:36.060 --> 1:01:38.827
Uh...

1:01:38.829 --> 1:01:41.129
- My wife.
- Hmm.

1:01:41.131 --> 1:01:44.032
- And your best?
- My wife.

1:01:47.738 --> 1:01:52.240
You know what?
I think this is better.

1:01:52.242 --> 1:01:54.342
Then it must have
been really bad.

1:01:54.344 --> 1:01:58.914
It lacked, uh... romance.

1:02:14.965 --> 1:02:16.898
Statton:
We're gonna get it back.

1:02:16.900 --> 1:02:19.000
You don't know that.

1:02:19.002 --> 1:02:20.368
Mmm. That's why we're here.

1:02:20.370 --> 1:02:23.872
- What?
- Father Donald's got it.

1:02:23.874 --> 1:02:25.874
Well, he had it.
He's getting it back.

1:02:25.876 --> 1:02:28.210
How did you find this out?

1:02:28.212 --> 1:02:30.746
Dec told me
in the police station.

1:02:30.748 --> 1:02:33.181
Dec told you?

1:02:33.183 --> 1:02:34.883
And why do you think
he'd do that, Statton?

1:02:34.885 --> 1:02:39.054
Because I paid him.

1:02:39.056 --> 1:02:43.358
You paid him? You paid him.

1:02:43.360 --> 1:02:46.027
What kind of fuckwittery
did they teach you

1:02:46.029 --> 1:02:47.896
in piano tuning school?

1:02:47.898 --> 1:02:50.365
Dec wants us dead,
and you just paid him

1:02:50.367 --> 1:02:53.535
to tell us where to go
so he could have us killed.

1:02:53.537 --> 1:02:56.238
Father Donald is a priest.
We can trust him.

1:02:56.240 --> 1:03:00.909
Dodgy Donald?
He's receiving stolen goods.
Think it through!

1:03:00.911 --> 1:03:04.513
He's a priest
that could afford
to bail us out.

1:03:04.515 --> 1:03:06.114
Come on, we gotta
get out of here.

1:03:09.219 --> 1:03:11.119
Fuck, I knew it!

1:03:12.055 --> 1:03:13.388
Sorry, Mary,
I thought that--

1:03:13.390 --> 1:03:15.423
Well, start thinking
of a way out.

1:03:15.425 --> 1:03:18.560
Sure, uh, um...

1:03:18.562 --> 1:03:21.396
- Windows!
- These windows are lead lined

1:03:21.398 --> 1:03:23.498
and too high
to climb out of anyway.

1:03:23.500 --> 1:03:26.368
No, no, we need to
attract attention.

1:03:26.370 --> 1:03:28.303
Uh...

1:03:39.583 --> 1:03:43.852
( playing
"House of Rising Sun" )

1:04:01.438 --> 1:04:04.339
Get up. Move.

1:04:06.610 --> 1:04:09.277
We've already been
to the police, Kipper.

1:04:09.279 --> 1:04:10.879
There's no point.

1:04:10.881 --> 1:04:13.315
Mary:
No point going down
for murder.

1:04:13.317 --> 1:04:15.617
It's only armed robbery.
No one got hurt.

1:04:15.619 --> 1:04:19.454
Dec says
if he gets armed robbery,
he goes down for twenty.

1:04:19.456 --> 1:04:23.158
Dec gets 20, I get dead,
kids-- no dad. Hmm?

1:04:23.160 --> 1:04:25.260
We'll refuse to testify.

1:04:27.464 --> 1:04:30.632
Dec's not the sort of guy
you could do a deal with.

1:04:30.634 --> 1:04:34.369
I don't want to do it.
I have to do it.

1:04:34.371 --> 1:04:40.275
- You don't have to do--
- I have to do it!

1:04:40.277 --> 1:04:44.212
Okay, okay.
You have to do it.

1:04:44.214 --> 1:04:50.452
But can we-- can we
at least talk awhile
before you do it?

1:04:52.990 --> 1:04:54.089
Sure.

1:05:01.431 --> 1:05:03.632
I want you to know that
I've never done this before.

1:05:03.634 --> 1:05:07.469
You don't have to
kill anyone today, Kipper.

1:05:07.471 --> 1:05:10.138
Mary:
You don't have to do
what Dec says.

1:05:10.140 --> 1:05:12.240
You're not the sidekick.

1:05:12.242 --> 1:05:15.343
Don't call me...

1:05:15.345 --> 1:05:17.679
an 'effing sidekick, okay?

1:05:17.681 --> 1:05:19.381
- I hate being a sidekick.
- I know, I know.

1:05:19.383 --> 1:05:21.016
Okay, I'm gonna do it.

1:05:21.018 --> 1:05:22.317
- Oh.
- Oh, no, no. No, no.

1:05:22.319 --> 1:05:23.618
I'm gonna do it
and then I'm gonna go.

1:05:23.620 --> 1:05:26.621
Okay.

1:05:26.623 --> 1:05:28.990
Just let me say
my prayers first.

1:05:28.992 --> 1:05:31.192
You still believe?

1:05:31.194 --> 1:05:33.261
Technically,
I'm still a nun.

1:05:33.263 --> 1:05:36.698
- Hmm? How?
- Well, I was never defrocked

1:05:36.700 --> 1:05:39.968
'cause I was just a novice,
so they didn't bother.

1:05:39.970 --> 1:05:41.536
Well, you were pretty well
defrocked tonight, love,
in the hotel.

1:05:41.538 --> 1:05:43.171
I saw you, okay?
Some nun you are.

1:05:43.173 --> 1:05:46.341
Lots of nuns sin, Kipper.
We're only human.

1:05:50.714 --> 1:05:53.214
Okay.

1:05:53.216 --> 1:05:55.417
Okay, ask for forgiveness.
Come on.

1:05:55.419 --> 1:05:57.452
And say one for me.

1:06:07.731 --> 1:06:13.635
Dear Lord, please forgive me
for my sins of the flesh.

1:06:15.238 --> 1:06:17.739
And, please,

1:06:17.741 --> 1:06:20.408
have mercy on the soul
of Kipper Jones.

1:06:20.410 --> 1:06:24.746
I know that Matthew 20:13 says

1:06:24.748 --> 1:06:27.582
that he who kills a nun
shall know no forgiveness,

1:06:27.584 --> 1:06:30.251
but instead will burn
in a fiery pit.

1:06:30.253 --> 1:06:32.253
But please, please,

1:06:32.255 --> 1:06:34.589
make an exception
in Kipper's case,

1:06:34.591 --> 1:06:36.658
for he knows not
what he does.

1:06:36.660 --> 1:06:41.730
- Did you hear that? Hey!
- Do you mind? I'm praying.

1:06:41.732 --> 1:06:44.132
Well, that's not
in the 'effing Bible.

1:06:44.134 --> 1:06:45.767
Sure it is.

1:06:45.769 --> 1:06:48.503
You think there's
no scripture covering
nun killers?

1:06:52.776 --> 1:06:55.276
And please, Lord,

1:06:55.278 --> 1:06:58.279
have mercy on Kipper's soul.

1:06:58.281 --> 1:07:03.451
I know that according to
your holy word in John 3:4,

1:07:03.453 --> 1:07:07.155
you say that the eyes
will be plucked out of the head

1:07:07.157 --> 1:07:10.158
of anyone who slays a nun

1:07:10.160 --> 1:07:12.227
or the protector of a nun.

1:07:12.229 --> 1:07:14.763
The protector of the nun?
It does not say that.

1:07:14.765 --> 1:07:17.799
Show me.
Show me where it says that
in the Bible.

1:07:17.801 --> 1:07:20.535
Show me in the passages
where those words are used.

1:07:20.537 --> 1:07:22.203
We don't have a Bible.

1:07:22.205 --> 1:07:23.638
But we're in
a bloody church, mate!

1:07:23.640 --> 1:07:25.473
Good point. Good point.
Good point.

1:07:25.475 --> 1:07:29.811
You, get over there.
Show me.

1:07:29.813 --> 1:07:32.313
Show me in that Bible.

1:07:32.315 --> 1:07:33.815
The holy Bible.

1:07:33.817 --> 1:07:35.183
Holy fuck.

1:07:35.185 --> 1:07:36.451
Move.

1:07:36.453 --> 1:07:40.088
Show me Matthew, John...

1:07:41.825 --> 1:07:45.260
Show me where it says
those words, huh?

1:07:49.833 --> 1:07:51.399
This Bible's in Latin.

1:07:52.669 --> 1:07:54.669
But that's what it means.

1:07:54.671 --> 1:07:57.105
I'm coming. I'm coming.

1:08:02.679 --> 1:08:09.517
<i>"Nonne ex denario</i>
<i>convenisti mecum."</i>

1:08:09.519 --> 1:08:12.420
<i>"Nonne"</i> means "nun."

1:08:12.422 --> 1:08:16.357
<i>"Ex denario"</i> means...

1:08:16.359 --> 1:08:18.526
<i>"Convenisti mecum."</i>

1:08:18.528 --> 1:08:20.762
"The convent's down a nun."

1:08:20.764 --> 1:08:22.530
<i>"Non facio tibi."</i>

1:08:22.532 --> 1:08:26.201
"The faceless man
who does this evil act."

1:08:28.238 --> 1:08:29.404
If you're lying to me--

1:08:29.406 --> 1:08:34.876
if you are lying to me...

1:08:34.878 --> 1:08:37.712
Why are they still here,
Kipper?

1:08:37.714 --> 1:08:40.615
How long can this
possibly take?

1:08:43.720 --> 1:08:45.887
Get out, get out! Huh?

1:08:45.889 --> 1:08:48.556
Okay, okay.

1:08:48.558 --> 1:08:50.258
- Stay there!
- Okay.

1:08:50.260 --> 1:08:53.461
Huh? Hey!

1:08:55.765 --> 1:08:56.831
You...

1:09:06.576 --> 1:09:08.676
I was gonna do it,
but I couldn't do it.
I'm sorry, Dec.

1:09:30.300 --> 1:09:34.435
- She's a nun.
- Yeah?

1:09:34.437 --> 1:09:36.671
Well, I'm a Methodist.

1:09:36.673 --> 1:09:39.307
- ( grunts )
- ( gunshot )

1:09:39.309 --> 1:09:41.409
( groaning )

1:09:41.411 --> 1:09:42.577
Statton!

1:09:45.182 --> 1:09:46.514
( groaning )

1:09:52.789 --> 1:09:54.222
Kipper:
I'm sorry, Dec.

1:09:54.224 --> 1:09:58.326
I couldn't let you do it.

1:09:58.328 --> 1:09:59.861
They're innocent.
I couldn't.

1:10:03.600 --> 1:10:05.200
( muttering )

1:10:08.972 --> 1:10:10.705
Oh! Kipper!

1:10:10.707 --> 1:10:13.808
Oh, Kipper! Kipper.

1:10:13.810 --> 1:10:16.411
Kipper:
I couldn't let him do it.
I couldn't.

1:10:16.413 --> 1:10:18.613
I couldn't let him do it.
It isn't right.

1:10:18.615 --> 1:10:21.482
( Kipper groaning )

1:10:21.484 --> 1:10:23.685
What in the name of Saint Tropez
is going on in here?

1:10:23.687 --> 1:10:25.520
Mother Superior,
call an ambulance!

1:10:25.522 --> 1:10:27.855
Call the police,
Father Donald.

1:10:27.857 --> 1:10:29.691
Call the ambulance.
Call the police.

1:10:29.693 --> 1:10:31.693
- ( Kipper groaning )
- Mary: Come here.

1:10:31.695 --> 1:10:34.896
- Oh.
- ( panting )

