Forget it.

1:11:15.872 --> 1:11:18.773
- Statton: Of course it does.
- Mary: It doesn't. Look...

1:11:21.411 --> 1:11:24.879
...when I was 18,
I stowed away on a ship.

1:11:24.881 --> 1:11:28.549
Stowed away?
What year was this, 1872?

1:11:28.551 --> 1:11:30.718
A cargo ship,

1:11:30.720 --> 1:11:35.056
to get here, because...

1:11:35.058 --> 1:11:37.425
this is where she lived.

1:11:37.427 --> 1:11:39.560
Your birth mother.

1:11:39.562 --> 1:11:44.632
And I thought she would be
so excited to meet me.

1:11:47.070 --> 1:11:52.907
Well, she refused to see me.

1:11:52.909 --> 1:11:55.576
Left me standing
at the front door.

1:11:55.578 --> 1:11:59.514
She basically
abandoned me again.

1:12:02.452 --> 1:12:03.818
Why are you back here?

1:12:08.458 --> 1:12:09.657
Really, why?

1:12:15.098 --> 1:12:16.998
She's dying, Statton.

1:12:20.770 --> 1:12:23.938
Her husband wrote me,
told me he'd get me in,

1:12:23.940 --> 1:12:25.106
that she should see me.

1:12:25.108 --> 1:12:27.575
"Should."
Should! Not "wants to."

1:12:27.577 --> 1:12:30.878
Things are different
when people are dying.

1:12:30.880 --> 1:12:33.948
Look, I don't even think
he told her I was coming.

1:12:33.950 --> 1:12:35.616
She probably would have
just rejected me

1:12:35.618 --> 1:12:37.385
and then died
right in front of me.

1:12:37.387 --> 1:12:40.388
Ah, she--
she might no reject you.

1:12:40.390 --> 1:12:42.490
Yes. Yes.

1:12:42.492 --> 1:12:44.492
And that's the comfort
I can live with

1:12:44.494 --> 1:12:45.960
for the rest of my life.

1:12:45.962 --> 1:12:49.964
I can live with uncertainty.
It's my specialty.

1:12:49.966 --> 1:12:53.634
What I can't live with is
a second round of rejection.

1:12:53.636 --> 1:12:56.504
I just can't.
And why should I?

1:12:56.506 --> 1:12:59.874
Why should I let her
make me feel like shit
on her deathbed?

1:13:01.978 --> 1:13:03.878
Well, it might not
feel like that.

1:13:06.149 --> 1:13:09.984
It might feel like...

1:13:09.986 --> 1:13:11.652
home.

1:13:11.654 --> 1:13:14.422
How do you know?

1:13:17.660 --> 1:13:23.531
Well, you know
adventure, Mary.

1:13:23.533 --> 1:13:26.901
Home is my forte.

1:13:57.133 --> 1:13:58.699
Gosh.

1:13:58.701 --> 1:14:01.569
- I'm--
- You're her...

1:14:01.571 --> 1:14:03.538
when I first met her.

1:14:05.742 --> 1:14:08.576
You can see her now.

1:14:08.578 --> 1:14:10.044
She's very ill.

1:14:10.046 --> 1:14:13.047
She'll only be able
to manage a short time.

1:14:23.193 --> 1:14:24.725
Hello.

1:14:28.031 --> 1:14:30.097
Oh, my gosh.

1:14:30.099 --> 1:14:32.834
( speaking Welsh )

1:14:32.836 --> 1:14:35.069
( continuing in Welsh )

1:14:35.071 --> 1:14:37.205
I'm sorry,
I'm not very good at Welsh.

1:14:37.207 --> 1:14:39.540
( speaking Welsh )

1:14:39.542 --> 1:14:41.909
I don't think
she knows who we are.

1:14:41.911 --> 1:14:43.244
She doesn't know
who anyone is.

1:14:43.246 --> 1:14:45.746
She's got dementia.

1:14:45.748 --> 1:14:47.748
Then why did you invite me

1:14:47.750 --> 1:14:49.884
if she doesn't know
who anyone is?

1:14:49.886 --> 1:14:52.253
I worried you wouldn't come.

1:14:52.255 --> 1:14:55.089
She can remember the past.

1:14:55.091 --> 1:14:58.259
She gets distressed at times.

1:14:58.261 --> 1:15:01.128
Please, I think
you might help her.

1:15:22.218 --> 1:15:23.784
You came.

1:15:29.292 --> 1:15:30.791
I came.

1:15:30.793 --> 1:15:34.128
David said
I need to give you advice

1:15:34.130 --> 1:15:36.664
for your honeymoon.

1:15:36.666 --> 1:15:38.132
The only thing
I can say is this,

1:15:38.134 --> 1:15:42.136
the best marriages
are those between

1:15:42.138 --> 1:15:45.139
an ocean
and a lighthouse.

1:15:45.141 --> 1:15:49.677
Two lighthouses are boring.

1:15:49.679 --> 1:15:52.680
Two oceans crash about.

1:15:52.682 --> 1:15:57.318
But a lighthouse
and an ocean

1:15:57.320 --> 1:15:59.186
will last forever.

1:16:00.757 --> 1:16:03.090
Take turns!

1:16:04.761 --> 1:16:07.929
Let him be the ocean
sometimes, darling.

1:16:07.931 --> 1:16:11.832
Turn your lights on
so he can find you.

1:16:11.834 --> 1:16:14.602
You don't have to be
the ocean all the time.

1:16:19.342 --> 1:16:21.242
No, no, no, don't take her!
Bring her back.

1:16:21.244 --> 1:16:23.344
It's just
a hot water bottle, Aurelie.

1:16:23.346 --> 1:16:24.779
Aurelie:
They've taken her!
Bring her back!

1:16:24.781 --> 1:16:28.015
- She's mine!
- No, I'm her.

1:16:28.017 --> 1:16:29.350
Aurelie, I'm her.

1:16:29.352 --> 1:16:30.952
Make them bring her back,
sister.

1:16:30.954 --> 1:16:34.889
I'm here. It's me.

1:16:34.891 --> 1:16:37.625
I'm her.

1:16:45.368 --> 1:16:47.101
Say my name.

1:16:51.207 --> 1:16:52.273
Mother.

1:16:55.044 --> 1:16:56.110
Yes.

1:17:03.753 --> 1:17:05.052
You're Charlotte.

1:17:07.890 --> 1:17:09.657
I'm Charlotte.

1:17:25.074 --> 1:17:26.307
Come with me.

1:17:28.244 --> 1:17:30.911
